This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring June 14th as Flag Day and the week beginning June 13th as National Flag Week. The proclamation highlights the significance and symbolism of the American flag as a representation of freedom and liberty. It mentions how the flag has been a unifying symbol throughout history, from the founding of the nation to its presence in various settings such as beaches, battlefields, and the uniforms of the military. The proclamation also emphasizes the flag's role in inspiring hope and serving as a source of pride for Americans. It concludes by calling upon citizens to display the flag and observe Flag Day and National Flag Week with pride and ceremony, as well as to honor America during the days leading up to Independence Day.